                            <comment id="12709664" author="sebb@apache.org" created="Fri, 15 May 2009 01:39:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Surely it&apos;s also possible for a directory entry to be neither a file nor a directory, so maybe the check should be:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
File.isFile() &amp;amp;&amp;amp; !File.isDirectory()
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;Later&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; A File may perhaps be neither but that&apos;s not relevant as we are only interested in whether an existing File is a directory or not.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12709691" author="trejkaz" created="Fri, 15 May 2009 03:49:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That may be true also.  The Java docs say it&apos;s impossible for both to be false, but I think that&apos;s also part of the same oversight as assuming they can&apos;t both be true.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12841652" author="sebb@apache.org" created="Fri, 5 Mar 2010 01:42:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Javadoc fixed; also updated code to use !File.isDirectory() rather than File.isFile():&lt;/p&gt;

